<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,610,870,933]" box="[151,301,907,933]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,292,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1375,1425,1951]" captionTargetId="figure-494@9.[151,1436,1425,1951]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 10–11. Paragrallomyia bifurcata n. sp. 10, female, lateral view;11, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401200/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Figs. 10–11</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,979,1407]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Description (female only): Body length 
<quantity box="[610,680,979,1005]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity box="[758,828,979,1005]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
. Head and abdomen black, thorax black. Palpus dark brown except for white outer face. Clypeus brown with sparse pale microsetulae. First flagellomere dark brown. Fronto-orbital plate dark brown. Row of katepisternal setae brownish. Fore tibia dark brown. Fore tarsus mostly white, tarsomere one brown on basal half only. Hind femur mostly brown, white on basal quarter and with a small angled preapical white ring. Tergites black. Oviscape black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,979,1407]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Head: First flagellomere covered by pale microsetulae. Frontal vitta with a darkened spot anterior to ocellar plate. Frontal vitta flat, not swollen anterior to ocellar plate. Epicephala converging, not immediately merging posterior to ocellar plate. Epicephalon somewhat swollen above frontal vitta level. Epicephalon somewhat swollen above frontal vitta level.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,979,1407]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Thorax: Mesonotum with lines of thin brownish microsetulae. Anterior half of postpronotal lobe bare. Femur covered with sparse black microsetulae. Mid and hind tibia almost cylindrical, sulcus on outer face weak. Cervical sclerite with a whitish oval swelling. Cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[632,658,1393,1407]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">4+5</subScript>
open at the tip of the wing.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401200" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4401200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401200/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" startId="9.[151,264,1974,1998]" targetBox="[151,1375,1425,1951]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1974,2034]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,339,1974,1998]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">FIGURES 10–11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ferro &amp; Marshall, 2020" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[345,606,1974,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[345,606,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Paragrallomyia bifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[612,670,1974,1998]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[612,670,1974,1998]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
10, female, lateral view;11, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
Abdomen: Single spermathecal duct with an apical small rounded swelling. Single spermatheca cylindrical and forked, with sparse small rounded processes (
<figureCitation box="[656,736,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1375,1425,1951]" captionTargetId="figure-494@9.[151,1436,1425,1951]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 10–11. Paragrallomyia bifurcata n. sp. 10, female, lateral view;11, female internal reproductive structures, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401200/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Paired spermathecal duct uniformly thick, slightly tapered on apical third before splitting into stems. Paired spermathecal duct stems uniformly thick, slightly convoluted. Paired spermathecae oval with an apical nipple-like swelling.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
